PyTorch's macros header forward-declares __assert_fail "matching glibc exactly"
(noexcept, unsigned int line) for CUDA/SYCL/ROCm device asserts. musl declares it
differently (_Noreturn, int line), so on musl the redeclaration conflicts:
  error: exception specification in declaration does not match previous declaration
We build LibTorch CPU-only, so this device-assert forward declaration is unnecessary;
gate the whole block to glibc. clang on musl does not define __GLIBC__.

Applies to PyTorch 2.12.x (torch/headeronly/macros/Macros.h). For older releases the
same block lives at c10/macros/Macros.h; the build script applies this best-effort
(git apply, warn-and-continue) so a path/line drift just no-ops. Apply with: git apply -p1
--
diff --git a/torch/headeronly/macros/Macros.h b/torch/headeronly/macros/Macros.h
index cef99df..a271fd4 100644
--- a/torch/headeronly/macros/Macros.h
+++ b/torch/headeronly/macros/Macros.h
@@ -486,7 +486,7 @@ __host__ __device__
            0);                                   \
   }
 #else // __APPLE__, _MSC_VER
-#if defined(NDEBUG)
+#if defined(NDEBUG) && defined(__GLIBC__)
 extern "C" {
 #if defined(__SYCL_DEVICE_ONLY__)
 extern SYCL_EXTERNAL void __assert_fail(
